WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.473 --> 00:00:07.841
<i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:07.941 --> 00:00:10.243
Brian Garrity is
a tinfoil hat-wearing truther.

3
00:00:10.310 --> 00:00:13.313
GARRITY:
FBI fabricated a manhunt to cover up

4
00:00:13.414 --> 00:00:16.817
the assassination of
Deputy Director Douglas Bailey.

5
00:00:16.917 --> 00:00:18.786
Do you have any idea
how many rabbit holes

6
00:00:18.886 --> 00:00:20.421
Brian Garrity has been down
in his life?

7
00:00:20.488 --> 00:00:23.957
The moon landing.
the Kennedy assassination.

8
00:00:24.057 --> 00:00:25.793
LEWIS: Guards say you're talking
to yourself.

9
00:00:25.893 --> 00:00:27.728
Anything I should know about?

10
00:00:30.297 --> 00:00:32.766
Go ahead. She'll believe you.

11
00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:36.336
Your subconscious
is fighting urges to kill.

12
00:00:36.470 --> 00:00:38.839
which is why
I'm distracting you.

13
00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:41.942
You talking to me
is how you cope.

14
00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:44.344
The families of some
of your victims have reached out

15
00:00:44.445 --> 00:00:45.713
and they want to meet you.

16
00:00:45.846 --> 00:00:47.314
Most are looking
for an accountability

17
00:00:47.381 --> 00:00:49.683
that doesn't always come
with a conviction.

18
00:00:49.817 --> 00:00:51.151
VOIT:
You think

19
00:00:51.251 --> 00:00:53.687
if I walk you
through everything.

20
00:00:53.821 --> 00:00:55.188
you'll be able
to stop someone else?

21
00:00:55.322 --> 00:00:56.890
LEWIS:
For the sake of others.

22
00:00:56.990 --> 00:01:00.160
I can't just let you sit
in here and not tell your story.

23
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:02.396
VOIT:
Problem is. while we sit in here

24
00:01:02.530 --> 00:01:04.465
talking about it. someone new

25
00:01:04.565 --> 00:01:06.066
is out there doing it.

26
00:01:06.166 --> 00:01:08.902
You just don't know it yet.

27
00:01:17.478 --> 00:01:19.713
Open up. Police.

28
00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:26.854
- What's his name again?
- Al Smith.

29
00:01:26.954 --> 00:01:29.957
Mr. Smith? Metro PD.

30
00:01:32.526 --> 00:01:34.795
- You're sure he's home?
- Think so.

31
00:01:34.895 --> 00:01:38.432
I saw him three days ago.
He's off.

32
00:01:38.532 --> 00:01:40.568
I-I need more than "he's off."

33
00:01:40.668 --> 00:01:44.337
He's not picking up his mail.
He's not answering his phone.

34
00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:47.808
Other day. he couldn't even
unlock his door.

35
00:01:47.908 --> 00:01:49.910
He's off.

36
00:01:50.043 --> 00:01:51.378
(keys jingle)

37
00:02:02.422 --> 00:02:04.424
Mr. Smith?

38
00:02:05.459 --> 00:02:07.394
- Anybody home?
- (soft hissing)

39
00:02:07.495 --> 00:02:10.230
We're entering
to do a wellness check.

40
00:02:10.330 --> 00:02:13.433
Sir? Are you all r...
(sniffs)

41
00:02:13.567 --> 00:02:15.335
Hold up.

42
00:02:15.435 --> 00:02:17.070
Is that a gas leak?

43
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.772
Our ranges are ancient.

44
00:02:18.872 --> 00:02:21.641
- Oh. no. did he suffocate?
- Shh. shh. shh.

45
00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:25.012
(sharp scratching in distance)

46
00:02:28.582 --> 00:02:31.619
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

47
00:02:31.719 --> 00:02:33.554
Hey. stop.

48
00:02:33.653 --> 00:02:35.155
Whoa. stop. Stop.

49
00:02:35.254 --> 00:02:37.024
What the fuck are you doing?

50
00:02:39.126 --> 00:02:40.561
Hey. what the fuck
are you doing? Stop.

51
00:02:40.628 --> 00:02:42.129
- You don't need to do this.
- Al.

52
00:02:42.262 --> 00:02:43.664
- no.
- Y-You don't need to do this.

53
00:02:43.764 --> 00:02:46.233
- BILL: Stop.
- KILPATRICK: No!

54
00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:52.205
♪ ♪

55
00:02:59.947 --> 00:03:02.149
♪

56
00:03:22.002 --> 00:03:24.204
♪ ♪

57
00:03:51.865 --> 00:03:53.867
I'm sorry.

58
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:57.470
(phone vibrates)

59
00:03:58.806 --> 00:04:00.741
(phone clicks)

60
00:04:11.284 --> 00:04:13.420
GARCIA:
Harlan Ellison wrote

61
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:14.922
"I have no mouth.

62
00:04:15.055 --> 00:04:17.791
and I must scream."

63
00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.501
(alarm ringing)

64
00:04:30.003 --> 00:04:31.639
Fuck!

65
00:04:33.073 --> 00:04:34.407
Fuck!

66
00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:41.514
(grunts)

67
00:04:41.581 --> 00:04:43.450
(ragged exhale)

68
00:04:51.524 --> 00:04:53.126
Fuck.

69
00:05:03.470 --> 00:05:05.338
Get it together.

70
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:25.793
(alarm stops)

71
00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:38.571
(elevator bell dings)

72
00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:43.476
- Where is he?
- He's right there.

73
00:05:43.576 --> 00:05:45.746
All right. Hey.

74
00:05:45.813 --> 00:05:49.449
- Thank you.
- Oh. but of course.

75
00:05:49.549 --> 00:05:53.353
- What happened to your hand?
- It's nothing. I'm okay.

76
00:05:58.658 --> 00:06:00.227
Holy shit!

77
00:06:00.327 --> 00:06:03.130
They will let anybody
up on the sixth floor now. huh?

78
00:06:03.196 --> 00:06:06.700
Well. they let your dumb ass
become a profiler. didn't they?

79
00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:08.368
- How have you been. Tom?
- Good.

80
00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:09.837
- Yeah?
- Good. You?

81
00:06:09.937 --> 00:06:11.004
Well. you know...

82
00:06:11.104 --> 00:06:14.708
Uh. listen. I-I. uh.
I heard about...

83
00:06:14.808 --> 00:06:17.144
- Yeah. Um...
- I know. bud.

84
00:06:17.244 --> 00:06:18.746
I'm sorry.

85
00:06:20.513 --> 00:06:22.682
Seriously. what. uh.
what are you doing up here?

86
00:06:22.783 --> 00:06:25.853
Well. I'm here to see you.
And. hopefully. your team.

87
00:06:25.986 --> 00:06:29.356
- Is it bad?
- It's weird.

88
00:06:29.456 --> 00:06:30.657
Come on.

89
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:32.459
Came to the right place.
Let's go.

90
00:06:32.525 --> 00:06:33.693
(chuckles)

91
00:06:33.827 --> 00:06:36.529
- Hey. SSA Prentiss.
- Hi.

92
00:06:36.629 --> 00:06:39.132
- Agent Tyler Green.
- Good to see you again. sir.

93
00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:40.834
Oh. you've worked
with Agent Green before?

94
00:06:40.901 --> 00:06:44.337
Well. I helped Green get through
his Basic Field Training Course.

95
00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:46.406
Well. he didn't help
so much as I survived.

96
00:06:46.539 --> 00:06:48.041
Agent Milliken kicked my ass.

97
00:06:48.141 --> 00:06:49.810
Me and all the new
agent trainees.

98
00:06:49.877 --> 00:06:51.211
PRENTISS:
Is that how you met Luke?

99
00:06:51.311 --> 00:06:54.815
Oh. no. Alvez and I
are retired army grunts.

100
00:06:54.882 --> 00:06:56.349
We met in the ARC Program.

101
00:06:56.449 --> 00:06:58.451
The Army Recovery Care Program.

102
00:06:58.551 --> 00:07:01.221
- They do great work.
- MILLIKEN: We do.

103
00:07:01.321 --> 00:07:03.223
I'm proud to get
to volunteer there.

104
00:07:03.323 --> 00:07:05.658
We help ill and injured
service members

105
00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:08.661
reintegrate into civilian life.

106
00:07:08.728 --> 00:07:11.899
Matter of fact. that's why
I'm knocking at your door.

107
00:07:12.032 --> 00:07:15.235
The BAU does equivocal
death investigations. correct?

108
00:07:15.335 --> 00:07:16.870
Helping determine
the manner of death.

109
00:07:16.937 --> 00:07:20.407
whether it's suicide.
homicide. or...

110
00:07:20.507 --> 00:07:21.775
just an accident?

111
00:07:21.875 --> 00:07:23.443
That is correct.
Do you have a case like that?

112
00:07:23.543 --> 00:07:24.411
Well...

113
00:07:24.511 --> 00:07:26.046
Luke. could you...

114
00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:29.716
This is Captain Al Smith.

115
00:07:29.817 --> 00:07:32.252
another friend of mine from ARC.

116
00:07:32.352 --> 00:07:34.321
He died yesterday morning.

117
00:07:34.421 --> 00:07:35.622
Cause of death?

118
00:07:35.755 --> 00:07:38.125
Gas stove blew up in his face.

119
00:07:38.225 --> 00:07:40.693
All four ranges
were turned all the way up.

120
00:07:40.794 --> 00:07:42.062
Based on the explosion.

121
00:07:42.129 --> 00:07:44.097
they'd been that way
for quite some time.

122
00:07:44.231 --> 00:07:46.299
Had the. uh. matchbook
in his hand.

123
00:07:46.433 --> 00:07:48.135
We can take the case.

124
00:07:48.268 --> 00:07:49.937
We'd start with
a psychological autopsy.

125
00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:52.372
but I-I just don't think
there's much for us

126
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:54.007
- to investigate here.
- MILLIKEN: I know. I know.

127
00:07:54.107 --> 00:07:56.443
And I know the numbers.
Hell. I preach 'em.

128
00:07:56.543 --> 00:07:59.947
87% of all vets report exposure
to at least one traumatic event.

129
00:08:00.047 --> 00:08:03.250
and less than half get
the treatment that they need.

130
00:08:03.350 --> 00:08:06.386
But that is not Al. okay?

131
00:08:06.453 --> 00:08:07.620
If you met him through ARC.

132
00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:09.056
what-what was he
being treated for?

133
00:08:09.156 --> 00:08:12.659
Anxiety. Depression.
Intrusive thoughts.

134
00:08:12.792 --> 00:08:16.129
Which are indicators of PTSD.

135
00:08:18.098 --> 00:08:20.733
His pistol was in his gun safe.

136
00:08:20.834 --> 00:08:23.703
I mean. he didn't blow his
brains out. he blew himself up.

137
00:08:23.803 --> 00:08:25.172
And he took a cop

138
00:08:25.305 --> 00:08:27.807
and a building superintendent
with him.

139
00:08:27.908 --> 00:08:30.610
That's odd. even for PTSD.

140
00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:33.146
Did you know him. Luke?

141
00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:35.015
I know the type.

142
00:08:35.147 --> 00:08:38.685
And I know what scares me is...

143
00:08:38.818 --> 00:08:41.021
Let's say this is
what it looks like.

144
00:08:41.121 --> 00:08:43.089
Sometimes.
it happens in clusters.

145
00:08:43.190 --> 00:08:45.458
One of our guys
punches his own ticket

146
00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:48.161
and another one says.
"Hey. that's a good idea."

147
00:08:48.295 --> 00:08:50.530
"Maybe I'll go out
the same way."

148
00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:53.700
That's why I want to take it.
Find out why.

149
00:08:54.634 --> 00:08:56.836
- Tyler. would you mind?
- Not at all.

150
00:08:56.970 --> 00:08:59.639
Agent Prentiss. thank you.

151
00:09:09.416 --> 00:09:12.019
- Good morning.
- Ugh.

152
00:09:12.119 --> 00:09:14.021
Ah. you got my email.

153
00:09:14.121 --> 00:09:16.656
What the hell is Voit up to?

154
00:09:16.756 --> 00:09:19.392
Tara is with him now.
so is Rebecca to expedite.

155
00:09:19.492 --> 00:09:21.995
All he has to do
is pick a family member

156
00:09:22.095 --> 00:09:24.397
and say. "Boo-hoo. I did it."

157
00:09:24.531 --> 00:09:26.033
Just one family member.

158
00:09:26.133 --> 00:09:29.102
And he is down
to his final four.

159
00:09:29.202 --> 00:09:32.472
He's treating this like he's
picking out a goddamn ring.

160
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:35.075
He is trying to find
the victim he killed

161
00:09:35.175 --> 00:09:36.676
with the least amount
of violence

162
00:09:36.776 --> 00:09:39.346
because that will be
the least upsetting

163
00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:40.580
to whomever he talks to.

164
00:09:40.713 --> 00:09:43.050
Yeah. well.
someone should tell him

165
00:09:43.150 --> 00:09:45.452
it's always upsetting.

166
00:09:49.489 --> 00:09:51.358
PRENTISS:
Hey. Morning.

167
00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:55.028
- Woof.
- Oh. You too?

168
00:09:57.097 --> 00:09:59.566
How many podcasts
do you listen to?

169
00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:02.702
Um. I don't know.
It's mostly news. Why?

170
00:10:02.802 --> 00:10:05.372
Well. Henry devours them.

171
00:10:05.472 --> 00:10:07.507
Specifically. the ones on Voit.

172
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:09.076
and it turns out
that there's one

173
00:10:09.176 --> 00:10:12.179
that mentions
me. you and the BAU.

174
00:10:12.279 --> 00:10:13.913
It's our case.

175
00:10:14.014 --> 00:10:16.483
- It goes with the territory
we'd be mentioned. - No.

176
00:10:16.583 --> 00:10:18.118
Emily.

177
00:10:18.218 --> 00:10:22.189
This one is made
by someone you know.

178
00:10:22.289 --> 00:10:24.791
Personally.

179
00:10:26.059 --> 00:10:27.260
Fu...

180
00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:29.162
(elevator bell dings)

181
00:10:29.362 --> 00:10:31.999
Emily. Bella!

182
00:10:32.099 --> 00:10:35.368
- Come on.
- Oh. Oh. dear. I get it.

183
00:10:35.502 --> 00:10:37.304
I've made your job harder.
haven't I?

184
00:10:37.370 --> 00:10:40.773
But. Emily. come on.
the brass ring is right there.

185
00:10:40.874 --> 00:10:42.943
All this time. I've been
barking up the wrong tree.

186
00:10:43.010 --> 00:10:45.178
I thought conspiracies
were where it's at.

187
00:10:45.278 --> 00:10:47.847
Serial killers.
Serial killers!

188
00:10:47.948 --> 00:10:50.450
My downloads
are through the roof.

189
00:10:50.550 --> 00:10:52.352
and it's not just
about the money.

190
00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:54.521
The money is very nice.

191
00:10:54.621 --> 00:10:56.389
It's about the social capital.

192
00:10:56.523 --> 00:10:59.692
Emily. I'm trending.
I've never trended before.

193
00:10:59.792 --> 00:11:01.294
I've never
had a hashtag catch on

194
00:11:01.361 --> 00:11:02.729
with more than three people

195
00:11:02.862 --> 00:11:04.064
and now I'm trending.

196
00:11:04.164 --> 00:11:06.033
And yes. of course.
I may have taken

197
00:11:06.133 --> 00:11:08.101
one or two little liberties

198
00:11:08.201 --> 00:11:10.904
in the service
of a greater story...

199
00:11:19.146 --> 00:11:20.813
Are you going to kill me?

200
00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:23.883
No. because that's illegal.

201
00:11:23.984 --> 00:11:27.020
And you have every right
to produce a podcast

202
00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:28.188
that is nothing but lies.

203
00:11:28.255 --> 00:11:31.391
Excuse me. not nothing.

204
00:11:31.491 --> 00:11:34.394
Did or did not Elias Voit
call you dad?

205
00:11:34.494 --> 00:11:38.131
Because I paid an orderly
a hefty sum for that intel.

206
00:11:39.967 --> 00:11:43.203
Which. when he said it.
was more like.

207
00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:44.571
uh. "Is that you. Dad?"

208
00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:46.273
And less like
I had it on the pod.

209
00:11:46.373 --> 00:11:49.376
which was more. um.
"Ooh. spank me. Daddy."

210
00:11:49.476 --> 00:11:52.112
PRENTISS:
Even that is not why you're here.

211
00:11:52.212 --> 00:11:54.247
You're here because
you're claiming

212
00:11:54.381 --> 00:11:55.748
Voit is a serial killer

213
00:11:55.848 --> 00:11:58.785
that was trained
by the BAU to be

214
00:11:58.918 --> 00:12:01.454
a Manchurian candidate.
which is-is...

215
00:12:01.588 --> 00:12:03.790
- uh... uh...
- ROSSI: It's horseshit.

216
00:12:03.923 --> 00:12:06.526
And you're gonna clean up
the mess you've made.

217
00:12:06.626 --> 00:12:09.462
I can do that.
I can do that. no problem.

218
00:12:09.596 --> 00:12:10.797
I-I'm wrapping up season one.

219
00:12:10.930 --> 00:12:13.633
I-I can put a cap
on the season finale.

220
00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:16.303
uh. and do a 180-degree pivot.

221
00:12:16.436 --> 00:12:17.937
That's what we do on podcasts.

222
00:12:18.038 --> 00:12:20.940
You start out with one thesis.
and then. eventually.

223
00:12:21.041 --> 00:12:23.810
you pivot to another one. right?

224
00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:26.746
To sell it. though.
I just need one

225
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:28.448
little thing.

226
00:12:28.548 --> 00:12:30.250
What?

227
00:12:30.317 --> 00:12:32.285
What no other
Elias Voit podcast has.

228
00:12:32.385 --> 00:12:33.953
I want
an on-the-record interview

229
00:12:34.054 --> 00:12:35.355
with the white whale himself.

230
00:12:35.455 --> 00:12:37.490
- You can't possibly...
- GARRITY: Oh. come on.

231
00:12:37.590 --> 00:12:38.725
I mean "white whale"
metaphorically.

232
00:12:38.791 --> 00:12:41.061
I'm not fat-shaming the guy.

233
00:12:41.161 --> 00:12:42.962
Although. I did hear
he's putting on LBs in prison.

234
00:12:43.063 --> 00:12:45.165
- Confirm? Deny?
- No.

235
00:12:45.265 --> 00:12:47.067
Okay. good for him.
Keeping the weight off.

236
00:12:47.134 --> 00:12:50.870
No to your request.
That's not happening.

237
00:12:50.970 --> 00:12:55.075
Oh... That's really a shame.

238
00:12:56.009 --> 00:12:57.810
I feel bad for you guys.

239
00:12:57.910 --> 00:13:00.647
'Cause I guess I'll just
have to keep telling my story

240
00:13:00.747 --> 00:13:02.515
my way.

241
00:13:06.753 --> 00:13:07.954
Get out.

242
00:13:10.690 --> 00:13:11.591
GARRITY:
Oh.

243
00:13:11.658 --> 00:13:14.861
Tell Tara I said hi.

244
00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:16.196
(sighs)

245
00:13:18.198 --> 00:13:20.300
OFFICER: Transfer van is here.
Please have

246
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:23.002
all transfer prisoners
to the garage and ready.

247
00:13:26.773 --> 00:13:29.209
I think this one.

248
00:13:29.342 --> 00:13:31.744
Oh. wait. no. sorry.

249
00:13:34.013 --> 00:13:35.882
No...

250
00:13:37.016 --> 00:13:38.685
This one. Yeah.

251
00:13:39.852 --> 00:13:42.055
- Deena Ryan.
- VOIT: Mm-hmm.

252
00:13:42.155 --> 00:13:43.123
You're sure?

253
00:13:43.223 --> 00:13:44.824
Yeah.

254
00:13:44.891 --> 00:13:46.526
- Yeah. I'm sure.
- LEWIS: Okay.

255
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:47.760
