nothing romantic about me.

768
00:37:40.325 --> 00:37:43.061
I'm not brilliant.
I'm not special.

769
00:37:43.161 --> 00:37:44.930
I'm an antisocial psychopath

770
00:37:45.030 --> 00:37:48.466
who can only get his heart rate
up by killing people.

771
00:37:48.567 --> 00:37:50.035
It's sad how pathetic I am.

772
00:37:50.135 --> 00:37:52.137
but you know
who's even more pathetic?

773
00:37:53.038 --> 00:37:55.106
Someone who makes a show
about it.

774
00:37:56.742 --> 00:37:59.144
And anyone who listens to it.

775
00:38:03.014 --> 00:38:04.816
Now we're done.

776
00:38:09.521 --> 00:38:11.322
(door opens)

777
00:38:13.191 --> 00:38:15.193
(door closes)

778
00:38:26.705 --> 00:38:28.106
(exhales)

779
00:38:29.474 --> 00:38:30.942
You knew that was gonna happen.

780
00:38:31.042 --> 00:38:33.244
You knew Voit was gonna do that.

781
00:38:33.344 --> 00:38:35.380
No. we told him
no physical contact.

782
00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:39.284
but yeah. I-I had a feeling
he would have something

783
00:38:39.384 --> 00:38:41.452
- up his sleeve.
- Mm-hmm.

784
00:38:42.921 --> 00:38:45.223
- (exhales)
- Hey. take it easy.

785
00:38:45.323 --> 00:38:48.359
I have to salvage the remains
of my flaming career.

786
00:38:48.459 --> 00:38:51.997
You betrayed me.
I thought we were friends.

787
00:38:52.764 --> 00:38:55.133
Oh. Brian. there's something
I've been wanting to say

788
00:38:55.233 --> 00:38:56.868
for the better part
of six years.

789
00:38:56.968 --> 00:38:59.004
We are not friends.

790
00:38:59.104 --> 00:39:02.040
All you have ever done
is make my life miserable.

791
00:39:02.140 --> 00:39:06.311
so my job is not
to make your job easier.

792
00:39:07.746 --> 00:39:10.448
Well. how dare you?

793
00:39:10.582 --> 00:39:12.017
You are a public servant.

794
00:39:12.117 --> 00:39:15.721
To the public!
Not to you. personally.

795
00:39:15.821 --> 00:39:17.522
Oh. you have me siding

796
00:39:17.623 --> 00:39:20.291
with a convicted serial killer
over you.

797
00:39:21.092 --> 00:39:23.261
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

798
00:39:23.361 --> 00:39:25.363
When my audience
hears this episode.

799
00:39:25.463 --> 00:39:28.700
they're gonna be furious
at Voit's disdain for them.

800
00:39:30.301 --> 00:39:32.270
You don't...

801
00:39:32.370 --> 00:39:34.339
have to post it.

802
00:39:35.140 --> 00:39:36.775
I already presold
the advertising

803
00:39:36.908 --> 00:39:40.545
to a vegan-only
meal kit delivery service.

804
00:39:40.612 --> 00:39:42.447
And if there's one group
you don't want to cross.

805
00:39:42.547 --> 00:39:44.382
it's Big Vegan.

806
00:39:44.482 --> 00:39:46.251
Okay. so. so.

807
00:39:46.317 --> 00:39:49.320
what if you reframed it?

808
00:39:49.420 --> 00:39:52.891
I mean. maybe this is
actually an opportunity.

809
00:39:52.958 --> 00:39:54.359
What do you mean?

810
00:39:54.459 --> 00:39:56.628
The podcast pivot.

811
00:39:56.728 --> 00:39:59.230
A-And didn't Voit
just hand you one

812
00:39:59.297 --> 00:40:01.132
on a silver platter?

813
00:40:02.634 --> 00:40:05.303
Yeah. Yeah.

814
00:40:06.972 --> 00:40:08.874
Uh. an episode where

815
00:40:08.974 --> 00:40:11.276
I find out the serial killer

816
00:40:11.376 --> 00:40:14.412
is just a serial killer.

817
00:40:14.512 --> 00:40:16.514
Oh. that's good.

818
00:40:16.614 --> 00:40:18.516
You are brilliant.

819
00:40:18.650 --> 00:40:20.919
(scoffs): Okay.
Thank you.

820
00:40:21.019 --> 00:40:22.153
I guess.

821
00:40:22.253 --> 00:40:25.691
Hearing that from you means...
something.

822
00:40:27.492 --> 00:40:29.060
(knocking)

823
00:40:32.764 --> 00:40:34.666
So... What. um.

824
00:40:34.800 --> 00:40:37.535
you decided
to kill him after all?

825
00:40:37.635 --> 00:40:38.904
I did not.

826
00:40:39.004 --> 00:40:42.040
But our Elias Voit
podcast problem

827
00:40:42.173 --> 00:40:43.875
has come to an end.

828
00:40:45.476 --> 00:40:47.412
(snoring)

829
00:40:49.915 --> 00:40:53.618
Nobody on Nguyen's patient list
comes close to the profile.

830
00:40:53.685 --> 00:40:56.221
But he did take a lot
of walk-ins who paid with cash

831
00:40:56.321 --> 00:40:57.723
because they didn't
have insurance.

832
00:40:57.856 --> 00:41:00.125
That's just like
the ARC program. right?

833
00:41:00.225 --> 00:41:02.560
I mean. this unsub is flying
just under the radar

834
00:41:02.694 --> 00:41:04.395
when it comes to victimology.

835
00:41:04.495 --> 00:41:06.497
MILLIKEN: Is there something about
his headaches that we missed?

836
00:41:06.597 --> 00:41:09.500
Some other condition
that he might have?

837
00:41:10.335 --> 00:41:11.703
Luke?

838
00:41:14.439 --> 00:41:15.640
Hmm?

839
00:41:15.707 --> 00:41:18.977
You got that "thinking
but not saying it" look.

840
00:41:19.044 --> 00:41:21.780
No. Uh...

841
00:41:23.048 --> 00:41:26.084
All right. what about this?
What about...

842
00:41:26.885 --> 00:41:28.887
...chronic traumatic
encephalopathy?

843
00:41:28.987 --> 00:41:30.188
CTE.

844
00:41:30.255 --> 00:41:31.890
Yeah. we are treating that
more and more.

845
00:41:31.990 --> 00:41:33.558
Especially as we understand
what concussions

846
00:41:33.658 --> 00:41:35.994
are doing to the brain.

847
00:41:36.094 --> 00:41:38.363
CTE has been known
to lead to violence.

848
00:41:38.463 --> 00:41:39.765
I mean. not always.

849
00:41:39.898 --> 00:41:41.366
- but yeah. sometimes.
- GREEN: And worst of all.

850
00:41:41.432 --> 00:41:42.934
it's like having a time bomb
in your head.

851
00:41:43.068 --> 00:41:45.436
Don't know you have it.
you can't even

852
00:41:45.536 --> 00:41:47.773
diagnose it until an autopsy.

853
00:41:48.539 --> 00:41:50.008
Do you think about that a lot?

854
00:41:50.942 --> 00:41:53.578
I mean. when you serve.
you're always thinking about

855
00:41:53.711 --> 00:41:55.814
where the next hit's
coming from.

856
00:41:55.914 --> 00:41:58.449
- Yeah.
- Our guy probably thought about it.

857
00:41:59.885 --> 00:42:01.753
And no matter where he goes.
he can't seem

858
00:42:01.853 --> 00:42:03.621
to get anybody to give him
a straight answer

859
00:42:03.721 --> 00:42:05.523
on why he's so angry
all the time.

860
00:42:05.623 --> 00:42:09.060
And each time he gets angry.
he loses more and more control.

861
00:42:09.127 --> 00:42:11.797
(voice fading): I mean. take
Nguyen. He shoved the ice pick

862
00:42:11.897 --> 00:42:13.464
so far up into the brain tissue.

863
00:42:13.564 --> 00:42:16.534
it made contact with the tip
of his skull. He's not trying...

864
00:42:16.634 --> 00:42:20.105
DOCTOR: I'm sorry. but I need to know
how you want to proceed.

865
00:42:20.205 --> 00:42:21.539
(exhales)

866
00:42:23.241 --> 00:42:24.542
Okay.

867
00:42:24.609 --> 00:42:26.778
Okay...

868
00:42:26.878 --> 00:42:28.579
I need to see her.

869
00:42:29.280 --> 00:42:30.548
Uh. b-before we do anything.

870
00:42:30.615 --> 00:42:32.884
I need to see her.
Where... Is she...

871
00:42:32.984 --> 00:42:34.953
- is she awake?
- She's sleeping.

872
00:42:35.053 --> 00:42:37.455
But I can wake her up for you.

873
00:42:39.724 --> 00:42:41.026
Is this my fault?

874
00:42:41.893 --> 00:42:44.429
- Is what your fault?
- If I would've brought her in

875
00:42:44.529 --> 00:42:47.432
sooner. maybe we'd have
found the tumor earlier.

876
00:42:47.498 --> 00:42:48.733
No.

877
00:42:48.800 --> 00:42:51.302
That's not how this works.

878
00:42:52.603 --> 00:42:55.173
No. No.

879
00:42:55.974 --> 00:42:58.309
That's not how this works.

880
00:42:59.310 --> 00:43:00.879
- What?
- ALVEZ: CTE.

881
00:43:00.979 --> 00:43:03.081
That's not how it works.
It's not how this unsub works.

882
00:43:03.181 --> 00:43:04.315
How do you know that?

883
00:43:04.449 --> 00:43:07.018
The violence
associated with CTE.

884
00:43:07.118 --> 00:43:08.619
you know. or cluster headaches
for that matter.

885
00:43:08.719 --> 00:43:11.089
it happens in bursts.

886
00:43:11.156 --> 00:43:13.224
It's disorganized. impulsive.

887
00:43:13.324 --> 00:43:16.694
Yeah. but this unsub
is stalking his victims.

888
00:43:16.794 --> 00:43:18.163
He's kidnapping them.

889
00:43:18.296 --> 00:43:21.299
Right. and then subjecting them
to sadistic torture.

890
00:43:21.399 --> 00:43:23.935
That's highly organized.

891
00:43:24.002 --> 00:43:25.470
So. you're saying that
he's not in pain at all?

892
00:43:25.570 --> 00:43:29.107
No. he is.
The victimology tells us that.

893
00:43:29.174 --> 00:43:30.541
Then what has the same symptoms?

894
00:43:30.675 --> 00:43:33.511
Matches cluster headaches or CTE
but is neither?

895
00:43:33.611 --> 00:43:35.713
A tumor.

896
00:43:36.614 --> 00:43:38.616
Like the Texas tower
shooter. um...

897
00:43:38.683 --> 00:43:40.585
- Charles Whitman.
- Yes.

898
00:43:40.685 --> 00:43:43.388
He had a tumor
pressing down on his amygdala.

899
00:43:43.521 --> 00:43:46.291
That's right. That's right.
Before he started shooting.

900
00:43:46.391 --> 00:43:48.293
he stabbed his wife and mother
to death.

901
00:43:48.393 --> 00:43:50.628
And in his suicide note.
he wrote

902
00:43:50.728 --> 00:43:53.264
that he knew there was
something wrong inside his head.

903
00:43:53.364 --> 00:43:54.832
MILLIKEN:
So. this soldier came to us

904
00:43:54.900 --> 00:43:58.103
for treatment. thinking
he had a headache. but...

905
00:43:58.203 --> 00:44:00.171
But he had something worse.

906
00:44:00.271 --> 00:44:01.940
Much worse.

907
00:44:19.590 --> 00:44:20.691
What the fuck?

908
00:44:20.791 --> 00:44:22.393
Hello. Doc.

909
00:44:29.434 --> 00:44:33.038
Hey. Our unsub
is Sergeant David Graham.

910
00:44:33.138 --> 00:44:34.539
Traffic cameras pinged him

911
00:44:34.639 --> 00:44:37.242
along with a passenger
we've ID'd

912
00:44:37.375 --> 00:44:39.477
as neurologist Dr. Mark Trank.

913
00:44:39.544 --> 00:44:41.846
All right. we have to assume
that's our next victim.

914
00:44:41.947 --> 00:44:43.915
- Anything else?
- MILLIKEN: Yeah. Graham bounced

915
00:44:44.049 --> 00:44:45.350
from ARC to the VA.

916
00:44:45.416 --> 00:44:47.485
A CAT scan revealed
a glioblastoma cluster

917
00:44:47.552 --> 00:44:49.554
- in his prefrontal cortex.
- Operable?

918
00:44:49.654 --> 00:44:51.456
Yeah. but risky. as in.

919
00:44:51.556 --> 00:44:53.691
"it might get
lobotomized" risky.

920
00:44:53.758 --> 00:44:55.493
VA doc that I talked to
said that Graham

921
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:57.728
refused to accept the diagnosis.

922
00:44:58.529 --> 00:45:01.332
- All right. Thanks.
- (elevator bell chimes)

923
00:45:02.200 --> 00:45:03.734
Alvez.

924
00:45:04.569 --> 00:45:06.404
We've lost too many men already.

925
00:45:06.504 --> 00:45:07.572
Copy?

926
00:45:07.672 --> 00:45:09.640
Copy.

927
00:45:33.231 --> 00:45:35.433
(grunts softly)

928
00:45:37.935 --> 00:45:39.971
Where the fuck am I?

929
00:45:45.876 --> 00:45:47.678
David.

930
00:45:52.317 --> 00:45:53.884
You remember me.

931
00:45:57.555 --> 00:45:59.624
I didn't think you would.

932
00:46:00.925 --> 00:46:03.128
But I remember you.

933
00:46:03.894 --> 00:46:05.696
You know what I remember?

934
00:46:07.565 --> 00:46:09.500
"I can fix you."

935
00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:11.402
That's what you said.

936
00:46:11.502 --> 00:46:14.139
"I can fix you. David."

937
00:46:15.073 --> 00:46:17.675
But you can't. can you?

938
00:46:18.576 --> 00:46:21.512
I said that I can try
to fix you.

939
00:46:21.612 --> 00:46:25.316
No. you said. "I can fix you."

940
00:46:25.416 --> 00:46:26.751
You lied.

941
00:46:29.320 --> 00:46:30.688
David.

942
00:46:31.889 --> 00:46:33.658
Your tumor is located

943
00:46:33.758 --> 00:46:36.694
inside the folds of your brain.

944
00:46:36.794 --> 00:46:39.197
I-I would never lie to you.

945
00:46:39.330 --> 00:46:41.866
Not if I have integrity

946
00:46:41.999 --> 00:46:43.368
as a doctor.

947
00:46:43.468 --> 00:46:45.236
Integrity?

948
00:46:49.006 --> 00:46:52.377
You want
to talk about integrity?

949
00:47:05.956 --> 00:47:07.258
Let's go. Breach silently.

950
00:47:07.358 --> 00:47:09.560
Follow our lead
once we're inside. Let's go.

951
00:47:09.660 --> 00:47:12.530
How well do you know your Bible?

952
00:47:18.002 --> 00:47:20.371
- (grunting)
- GRAHAM: Let me tell you

953
00:47:20.471 --> 00:47:22.773
what I've learned
about integrity.

954
00:47:30.415 --> 00:47:32.083
(softly):
Go. go. go.

955
00:47:35.052 --> 00:47:37.021
The men who trained me...

956
00:47:37.122 --> 00:47:39.624
you know what they drilled
into me. huh?

957
00:47:40.858 --> 00:47:43.928
"Sergeant Graham.
what is the NCO Creed. soldier?"

958
00:47:44.061 --> 00:47:45.730
"Sir. to never compromise
my integrity

959
00:47:45.863 --> 00:47:47.965
or my moral courage. sir."

960
00:47:48.065 --> 00:47:49.867
"Soldier. what is integrity?"

961
00:47:49.934 --> 00:47:52.069
"Sir. integrity means
you will do and say nothing

962
00:47:52.170 --> 00:47:53.671
that deceives others. sir."

963
00:47:53.771 --> 00:47:55.573
You have no integrity.

964
00:47:55.673 --> 00:47:58.276
"I can fix you."
That's what you fucking said.

965
00:47:58.376 --> 00:48:00.878
Now it's my turn to fix you.

966
00:48:00.945 --> 00:48:02.980
"You need not fear
the terror of the night.

967
00:48:03.080 --> 00:48:05.216
"Or the arrow that flies by day.

968
00:48:05.316 --> 00:48:09.520
Though thousands fall about you.
near you it shall not touch."

969
00:48:10.455 --> 00:48:12.757
Know that one. David?

970
00:48:13.591 --> 00:48:17.328
My squads used to pray that
when we'd go out on patrol.

971
00:48:18.763 --> 00:48:20.431
Psalm 91.

972
00:48:20.565 --> 00:48:22.267
That's right.

973
00:48:22.367 --> 00:48:24.202
Soldier's Prayer.

974
00:48:25.770 --> 00:48:26.904
You serve?

975
00:48:27.004 --> 00:48:28.306
Yeah. I did.

976
00:48:28.406 --> 00:48:31.008
And so did my partner here.

977
00:48:31.108 --> 00:48:34.111
You know. I've been
praying Psalm 91 a lot.

978
00:48:37.047 --> 00:48:39.016
Hasn't done much good.

979
00:48:39.116 --> 00:48:41.186
I know.

980
00:48:41.952 --> 00:48:44.021
I know how you feel.

981
00:48:50.127 --> 00:48:53.331
When I got back
from my last tour...

982
00:48:55.333 --> 00:48:58.503
...I was losing my shit
all the time.

983
00:49:01.105 --> 00:49:04.842
At one point.
I even had my gun in my mouth.

984
00:49:06.244 --> 00:49:09.747
I know what that metal
feels like against your teeth.

985
00:49:12.016 --> 00:49:14.252
I'm guessing you do. too.

986
00:49:15.886 --> 00:49:17.555
Yeah. I do.

987
00:49:18.856 --> 00:49:21.692
But I realized it wouldn't
make me feel any better.

988
00:49:23.160 --> 00:49:24.695
But this?

989
00:49:25.530 --> 00:49:28.866
- This does.
- I know.

990
00:49:31.302 --> 00:49:32.737
I know.

991
00:49:34.505 --> 00:49:37.708
So how come you're where you are

992
00:49:37.808 --> 00:49:39.844
and I'm where I am?

993
00:49:42.947 --> 00:49:45.149
I went to a ARC.

994
00:49:46.517 --> 00:49:48.853
I asked for help.

995
00:49:48.986 --> 00:49:51.021
I tried that.

996
00:49:53.291 --> 00:49:54.859
I know.

997
00:49:57.528 --> 00:49:59.630
So what makes you so lucky. huh?

998
00:50:00.531 --> 00:50:02.567
What'd they do for you?

999
00:50:05.870 --> 00:50:07.738
They paired me up.

1000
00:50:09.807 --> 00:50:13.010
Yeah? With who?

1001
00:50:14.712 --> 00:50:16.747
Someone I just lost.

1002
00:50:28.426 --> 00:50:29.760
Hey.

1003
00:50:31.762 --> 00:50:33.230
Hey.

1004
00:50:33.331 --> 00:50:35.533
(whimpers softly)

1005
00:50:41.105 --> 00:50:43.574
Let me ask you something.

1006
00:50:43.674 --> 00:50:46.076
Does that even
make a difference?

1007
00:50:47.812 --> 00:50:49.880
You having a buddy?

1008
00:50:51.248 --> 00:50:52.850
Yeah.

1009
00:50:54.852 --> 00:50:57.855
Yeah. she made a difference.
She made a...

1010
00:50:57.955 --> 00:51:00.157
made a big difference.

1011
00:51:02.727 --> 00:51:05.430
What the fuck now. huh?

1012
00:51:05.530 --> 00:51:08.032
You gonna be my buddy?

1013
00:51:09.099 --> 00:51:12.403
You gonna come visit me
in prison after all this?

1014
00:51:13.438 --> 00:51:14.639
After all this?

1015
00:51:14.739 --> 00:51:17.475
What are we gonna do. buddy?

1016
00:51:17.575 --> 00:51:19.477
Trade war stories in the yard?

1017
00:51:19.610 --> 00:51:22.913
Hey. if that's
what you want. I will.

1018
00:51:23.013 --> 00:51:25.082
- (whimpers)
- I will.

1019
00:51:30.655 --> 00:51:33.324
I just don't want
to hurt anymore.

1020
00:51:34.759 --> 00:51:36.527
I know.

1021
00:51:38.829 --> 00:51:41.699
But I can't let you hurt
anyone else. either. okay?

1022
00:51:41.799 --> 00:51:43.233
Okay...

1023
00:51:43.300 --> 00:51:45.269
Just put down the ice pick.

1024
00:51:46.804 --> 00:51:50.808
I don't want to see
anyone else die this week.

1025
00:51:51.642 --> 00:51:52.643
Okay?

1026
00:51:52.743 --> 00:51:54.879
Please.

1027
00:51:56.481 --> 00:51:58.483
Put it down.

1028
00:51:58.616 --> 00:52:00.418
Okay?

1029
00:52:02.420 --> 00:52:03.521
(ice pick clatters)

1030
00:52:03.621 --> 00:52:05.823
Hey.
It's clear.

1031
00:52:05.923 --> 00:52:07.492
Hey.

1032
00:52:07.592 --> 00:52:10.227
I'm not bullshitting you.

1033
00:52:11.529 --> 00:52:15.032
You want to talk to another
soldier. I'll be there for you.

1034
00:52:16.567 --> 00:52:18.035
I mean that.

1035
00:52:19.003 --> 00:52:20.805
What was her name?

1036
00:52:21.839 --> 00:52:24.509
The one they paired you up with.

1037
00:52:26.143 --> 00:52:27.945
Roxy.

1038
00:52:28.979 --> 00:52:30.915
Her name was Roxy.

1039
00:52:41.759 --> 00:52:43.193
Just hang on. all right?

1040
00:52:43.327 --> 00:52:45.062
- Let me get you out right now.
- TRANK: Okay.

1041
00:52:45.963 --> 00:52:49.099
- (whines)
- There's my girl.

1042
00:52:56.474 --> 00:52:59.209
You remember
the first day we met?

1043
00:52:59.309 --> 00:53:00.878
Hmm?

1044
00:53:01.011 --> 00:53:03.213
They told me. they said...

1045
00:53:03.347 --> 00:53:05.716
they said. "Be careful.

1046
00:53:05.816 --> 00:53:07.985
She's a handful."

1047
00:53:08.819 --> 00:53:10.621
And I said. "Good.

1048
00:53:12.156 --> 00:53:14.759
'Cause I am. too."

1049
00:53:15.560 --> 00:53:16.961
(whimpers softly)

1050
00:53:20.230 --> 00:53:22.567
You saved my life.

1051
00:53:22.700 --> 00:53:24.902
(crying softly)

1052
00:53:26.270 --> 00:53:28.439
(door opens)

1053
00:53:29.239 --> 00:53:31.442
(Roxy whimpering softly)

1054
00:53:48.258 --> 00:53:50.461
♪ ♪

1055
00:54:13.050 --> 00:54:15.720
GARCIA: "Because he holds fast
to me in love.

1056
00:54:15.820 --> 00:54:17.254
"I will deliver him.

1057
00:54:17.354 --> 00:54:20.725
I will protect him
because he knows my name."

1058
00:54:20.825 --> 00:54:22.993
Psalm 91.

1059
00:54:25.162 --> 00:54:27.765
ROSSI:
I liked your little show.

1060
00:54:27.865 --> 00:54:29.333
For the podcast.

1061
00:54:29.433 --> 00:54:33.070
Performative violence.
Nice touch.

1062
00:54:33.170 --> 00:54:35.205
Yeah. sometimes you got to
give the people what they want.

1063
00:54:35.305 --> 00:54:38.843
Scare 'em and just pull
the carpet out from under them.

1064
00:54:38.943 --> 00:54:41.311
Sure. You're not a monster.

1065
00:54:41.445 --> 00:54:43.213
You're pathetic.

1066
00:54:43.313 --> 00:54:45.315
Which means you don't
have to tell anyone

1067
00:54:45.415 --> 00:54:48.085
what you really did
to Deena Ryan.

1068
00:54:48.152 --> 00:54:50.354
(choking)

1069
00:54:57.094 --> 00:54:58.162
VOIT:
Stop.

1070
00:54:58.295 --> 00:54:59.597
Oh. look at that.

1071
00:54:59.664 --> 00:55:01.999
You can shut me up.

1072
00:55:02.099 --> 00:55:05.169
Maybe you're not as pathetic
as you let on.

1073
00:55:05.269 --> 00:55:07.605
- Yeah. maybe.
- Maybe.

1074
00:55:07.705 --> 00:55:09.940
But then. what was the point
of defanging yourself?

1075
00:55:10.040 --> 00:55:13.277
Was that for the. um.
listening audience

1076
00:55:13.377 --> 00:55:15.680
or the BAU?

1077
00:55:17.347 --> 00:55:19.416
(clanging in distance)

1078
00:55:20.985 --> 00:55:22.386
Wait a minute.

1079
00:55:23.287 --> 00:55:25.455
Wait a minute.

1080
00:55:25.556 --> 00:55:27.992
Is that what this is all about?

1081
00:55:28.058 --> 00:55:30.527
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1082
00:55:30.628 --> 00:55:32.630
You're analyzing this cell.

1083
00:55:32.697 --> 00:55:36.533
Every guard. every door.
every vulnerability.

1084
00:55:36.634 --> 00:55:37.868
That's not true.

1085
00:55:38.002 --> 00:55:40.137
I pled guilty.
I'm gonna pay for what I did.

1086
00:55:40.237 --> 00:55:41.305
Hey.

1087
00:55:41.371 --> 00:55:43.674
You can lie
to your conscious self.

1088
00:55:43.741 --> 00:55:45.910
but you can't lie to me.

1089
00:55:46.043 --> 00:55:49.279
You're planning on your chance

1090
00:55:49.379 --> 00:55:51.281
to escape.

1091
00:55:54.018 --> 00:55:56.553
GARRITY:
So. we give Elias Voit

1092
00:55:56.687 --> 00:55:58.522
the last word.

1093
00:55:58.623 --> 00:56:01.826
He wanted us to know
how he feels.

1094
00:56:01.892 --> 00:56:04.428
We owe him our attention.

1095
00:56:04.561 --> 00:56:06.797
if not our approval.

1096
00:56:08.465 --> 00:56:11.368
For the last time.
this is Brian Garrity.

1097
00:56:11.468 --> 00:56:15.439
Thank you for listening
to The Sicarius Files.

1098
00:56:16.941 --> 00:56:18.776
VOIT:
There's...

1099
00:56:18.876 --> 00:56:21.812
nothing romantic about me.

1100
00:56:21.912 --> 00:56:24.548
I'm not brilliant.
I'm not special.

1101
00:56:24.649 --> 00:56:26.751
I'm an antisocial psychopath

1102
00:56:26.851 --> 00:56:30.020
who can only get his heart rate
up by killing people.

1103
00:56:31.421 --> 00:56:33.090
It's sad how pathetic I am.

1104
00:56:33.190 --> 00:56:34.992
but you know
who's even more pathetic?

1105
00:56:36.260 --> 00:56:38.528
Someone who makes
a show about it.

1106
00:56:38.629 --> 00:56:41.598
And anyone who listens to it.
